episodes.title: Chardee MacDennis 2: Electric Boogaloo
episodes.plot: The foursome demonstrate Chardee MacDennis for an interested board game executive.

episodes.title: Frank Falls Out the Window
episodes.plot: After falling out of the window, Frank thinks that it's 2006; the other three see this as a do-over.

episodes.title: The Gang Hits the Slopes
episodes.plot: Dennis and Frank square off against Dee and Mac for control of the mountain, while Charlie learns that the slopes have their own set of rules.

episodes.title: Dee Made a Smut Film
episodes.plot: The Gang debates modern art after seeing Dee in a smut film; Mac and Charlie enlist the help of Frank and Cricket in order to prove that modern art is worthless, whilst Dee and Dennis adapt his erotic memoirs to prove that it isn't.

episodes.title: Mac & Dennis Move to the Suburbs
episodes.plot: Dennis and Mac head to the suburbs for cheap rent and open spaces but quickly find out that they are meant for city life.

episodes.title: Being Frank
episodes.plot: A day in the life of Frank Reynolds as he tries to keep up with the gang's newest scheme.

episodes.title: McPoyle vs. Ponderosa: The Trial of the Century
episodes.plot: Liam McPoyle teams up with the lawyer to sue Bill Ponderosa for his lost eye; old grievances resurface.

episodes.title: Charlie Catches a Leprechaun
episodes.plot: Dennis tries to create an innovative mobile Paddy's pub experience but runs into trouble when customers refuse to cooperate, while Charlie and Mac attempt to catch a thieving leprechaun.

episodes.title: The Gang Goes to Hell
episodes.plot: The gang board a Christian cruise liner under upon Mac's request, to soon find out that it does not cater to their sinful ways.

episodes.title: The Gang Goes to Hell: Part Two
episodes.plot: The gang gets real with one another in the face of death.
